The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sarda blow

 Calcutta, Oct. 17: The bail plea of Govind Sarda, who has been arrested on the charge of supplying expired and faulty medical kits, was rejected by the chief metropolitan magistrates court today.

 His bail petition was rejected and he was remanded in judicial custody till October 27, said Gyanwant Singh, deputy commissioner, detective department.

 Our teams have rushed to Siliguri, Burdwan and Bankura to raid hospitals and blood banks. Sardas company had supplied such kits to private hospitals and diagnostic centres in the city as well in the three districts, Singh added.

 Health secretary Kalyan Bagchi met police chief Prasun Mukherjee yesterday and discussed the issue.




